# Auto-push to `dev`

Mobile testing is the live `/MartinOverdrive/dev/` PWA. Unpushed work is invisible on the phone.

## Default after finishing work on `dev`

1. Commit the relevant changes (skip junk like `fill_page.html`, secrets, local-only notes).
2. Push with bare `git push` (never `git push origin main`).
3. Confirm the Pages deploy for that commit (`gh run list --workflow deploy-pages.yml --limit 3`) when the user needs it live, or when verifying the change.

Do this **without waiting to be asked**, unless a strong reason below applies.

## Strong reasons to NOT push (ask first)

- Build / validate fails
- Secrets or credentials in the diff
- User explicitly said not to commit or push
- Destructive git ops (force push, reset, amend of pushed commits)
- Change belongs only on `main` or another branch, or would break the linear `dev` → `main` ff-only promote
- You're mid-task and the tree is intentionally half-done (push when the slice is usable on phone)

## Notes

- Prefer small, phone-testable pushes over holding a large local stack.
- The SW update banner only helps after this feature itself is deployed; until then, hard-refresh once after the first push of banner-related work.
